All Classes

Class Description
ArrayBiterator
Implementation of SizedBiterator used to stream all values within a specified integer array representing indices in an order appropriate to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
Biterator
Bit Iterating implementation of Spliterator that is meant to be used in conjunction with BitSets.
BitSet
Representation a fixed number of bits stored within an internal long array, mapping positive integer indices to individual bits and facilitating the manipulation of those individual bits or ranges of bits, as well as retrieving their boolean values.
BitSetBiFunction
Functional interface used to apply functions to a BitSet using a second BitSet.
BitSetFunction
Functional interface used to apply functions to a BitSet.
ConcurrentBitSet
Implementation of BitSet in which all methods capable of reading or writing the state of bits are delegated to concurrent-safe operations.
DeadBiterator
Implementation of Biterator used to stream the indices of dead bits within a BitSet, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
DensityRandom
Implementation of Random which generates bits with a specified Hamming-weight ratio using a sequence of bitwise AND and OR operations.
ImmutableBitSet
Implementation of BitSet causing ImmutableBitSet.setWord(int, long), which controls all write operations, to throw an UnsupportedOperationException.
InlineBitSet
Implementation of BitSet in which most methods are manually inlined to increase performance by reducing the overhead from the call-stack at the cost of readability.
LiveBiterator
Implementation of Biterator used to stream the indices of live bits within a BitSet, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
Matrix
64 by 64 bit matrix backed by either a BitSet, ConcurrentBitSet or ImmutableBitSet.
MatrixFunction
Functional interface used to apply functions to a Matrix.
Random
Pseudo-random number generator using a modified version of the (not cryptography-secure) XORShift64 algorithm to generate uniform random numbers.
RangeBiterator
Implementation of SizedBiterator used to stream all indices of a specified range, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel.
SizedBiterator
Implementation of Biterator that is meant to be used when streaming a known number of indices.
WordBiFunction
Functional interface used in conjunction with BitSet.apply(int, WordBiFunction, long).
WordFunction
Functional interface used in conjunction with BitSet.apply(int, WordFunction).
